text: I love Cafe Society. It really evokes that 1930s Hollywood scene, esp with the beige tones. The awkwardness in the scene when he gets the hooker but they don't feel like doing it, is quite a scream. Even if you had a rich successful uncle in the industry like Steve Correll's character, would a nephew from working-class jews in NYC really get elevated to the pinnacle of beautiful society like he did? Arguable. A tad far-fetched like a Sidney Sheldon novel, but still a great film. I watched it and drank in the realism and the beauty of the settings. A lot of that jewish family stuff is really funny. Another triumph for woody Allen!
